Noyer Says Restoring Confidence May Re-Start Growth in 2012

-- B y   M a r k   D e e n
-- 
2011-10-16T17:01:12Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-16/noyer-says-restoring-confidence-may-re-start-growth-in-2012.html
Bank of France Governor Christian
Noyer said that European governments can boost growth next year
by restoring confidence to households and businesses. He said
that growth has slowed though an outright recession is unlikely.
He spoke on TV5 Monde.  To contact the reporter on this story:
